<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-09-13T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-09-13T17:00:00-05:00" n="589" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d589">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5231/1024: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-09-13T18:00:00-04:00">September 13, 1935—6
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>57. Your 58, September 13, 1 p.m. Calderón presented on September 6 a
                                final list<note n="19" xml:id="d589fn19">Not printed.</note> of
                                Spanish concessions increasing the automobile quota allotment to
                                3,363,619 kilograms but refusing all the other American requests of
                                which you were informed in the Department’s telegram No. 51 of
                                August 8, 6 p.m.</p>
                            <p>The Department has not yet reached a decision but is giving all
                                aspects of the situation the most careful and detailed consideration
                                and is bearing in mind the points brought out by you in your
                                telegram No. 48 of July 18.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>